WEBVTT

1
00:00:49.167 --> 00:00:51.375
[MEN SPEAKING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

2
00:01:40.625 --> 00:01:43.708
[MEN SPEAKING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

3
00:01:46.625 --> 00:01:48.250
[BOTH GRUNTING]

4
00:01:57.083 --> 00:01:59.542
[ALL GRUNTING]

5
00:02:04.667 --> 00:02:06.917
[MEN SHOUTING]

6
00:02:16.708 --> 00:02:18.958
[GRUNTING]

7
00:02:22.750 --> 00:02:25.708
Jackson, you going
to be going to Hong Kong?

8
00:02:25.875 --> 00:02:29.042
I love anything with full contact.
Need a few more scars.

9
00:02:29.208 --> 00:02:31.167
I heard you get killed
at that <i>kumite.</i>

10
00:02:31.333 --> 00:02:33.375
Only if you fuck up.

11
00:02:37.208 --> 00:02:39.167
[BOTH GRUNT]

12
00:02:39.333 --> 00:02:41.125
[LAUGHS]

13
00:02:45.292 --> 00:02:47.708
Tomorrow, we leave for the <i>kumite.</i>

14
00:03:07.583 --> 00:03:10.000
Sir?

15
00:03:10.167 --> 00:03:12.750
Excuse me, but Colonel Cooke
would like to see you

16
00:03:12.917 --> 00:03:15.792
- before you leave on furlough.
- What's the problem?

17
00:03:15.958 --> 00:03:19.875
The colonel found out you're going
to Hong Kong. He wants to talk to you.

18
00:03:20.042 --> 00:03:23.292
Tell him I'll be right there...
after I take a shower.

19
00:03:23.458 --> 00:03:26.708
- But I'll have to wait, sir.
- OK.

20
00:03:31.208 --> 00:03:33.417
What's taking so long, Captain?

21
00:03:34.125 --> 00:03:35.250
[WATER RUNNING]

22
00:03:35.417 --> 00:03:36.833
Captain?

23
00:03:47.375 --> 00:03:48.708
Shit!

24
00:04:08.000 --> 00:04:10.542
- Sir!
- Where's Dux?

25
00:04:10.708 --> 00:04:11.958
He was in the gym.

26
00:04:12.125 --> 00:04:14.375
He took a shower, I waited,
he disappeared.

27
00:04:14.542 --> 00:04:15.833
What do you mean?!

28
00:04:16.000 --> 00:04:18.417
One minute he was there,
the next, he wasn't.

29
00:04:18.583 --> 00:04:20.458
If anything happens in Hong Kong...

30
00:04:20.625 --> 00:04:23.000
Get Helmer and Rawlins
on this right away!

31
00:04:23.167 --> 00:04:27.125
And I don't want to see your face
again until Dux is beside it!

32
00:04:45.333 --> 00:04:46.417
[SIGHS]

33
00:04:46.583 --> 00:04:48.708
- How is he?
- He's resting now.

34
00:04:48.875 --> 00:04:53.708
- He'll be so happy to see you.
- It's so good to be here again.

35
00:04:56.792 --> 00:05:00.250
- I tell him you're here.
- Thank you.

36
00:05:20.292 --> 00:05:22.458
BOY 1: Wow, look at the sword!

37
00:05:29.042 --> 00:05:30.125
BOY 2: Let's get it!

38
00:05:30.292 --> 00:05:33.250
Come on, Frank.
What's the matter, you chicken?

39
00:05:33.417 --> 00:05:35.125
- No.
- BOY 1: Then get in here!

40
00:05:35.292 --> 00:05:38.708
BOY 2: Hey, Frank, you want to
hang out with us, then come on!

41
00:05:41.833 --> 00:05:44.250
You just going to stand there,
or are you going to grab something?

42
00:05:44.417 --> 00:05:45.250
[DOOR OPENS]

43
00:05:45.417 --> 00:05:47.958
Shit! They're coming back!
Let's get out of here!

44
00:05:48.125 --> 00:05:51.375
- Come on, Frank!
- BOY 2: Forget him. Let's go!

45
00:06:10.083 --> 00:06:13.417
That's enough, Shingo.
Go to your studies.

46
00:06:23.792 --> 00:06:27.583
You cannot get katana sword by stealing.

47
00:06:27.750 --> 00:06:30.500
It is a very special sword.

48
00:06:31.500 --> 00:06:35.208
- You must earn it.
- I wasn't going to steal it.

49
00:06:41.042 --> 00:06:44.375
You didn't flinch.
You have fighting spirit.

50
00:06:44.542 --> 00:06:49.292
- You're not going to call the cops?
- Not if we make a deal.

51
00:06:49.458 --> 00:06:51.542
What kind of a deal?

52
00:06:51.708 --> 00:06:55.208
TANAKA: Your son and my son
are in the same school.

53
00:06:55.375 --> 00:06:57.917
Frank sees my son's skill,

54
00:06:58.083 --> 00:07:01.708
and he desires to learn
martial science, too.

55
00:07:01.875 --> 00:07:06.375
MR. DUX: Yes, but what do you mean
by "martial science"?

56
00:07:06.542 --> 00:07:10.375
Frank's told me you came
to America to grow vine.

57
00:07:10.542 --> 00:07:13.000
Yes, that's right.
I work at the Verne Vineyard.

58
00:07:13.167 --> 00:07:16.583
I came here to grow fish
in my hatchery.

59
00:07:16.750 --> 00:07:19.542
We both grow children.

60
00:07:19.708 --> 00:07:23.042
You use science
to make vines grow better.

61
00:07:23.208 --> 00:07:26.917
Like vines, children need training.

62
00:07:27.083 --> 00:07:30.833
Martial science provide
a way of training.

63
00:07:31.000 --> 00:07:35.125
Brings mind, body, spirit together.

64
00:07:40.250 --> 00:07:41.958
That's enough!

65
00:07:42.125 --> 00:07:44.375
- That's all for today.
- Not yet.

66
00:07:44.542 --> 00:07:46.583
Why don't you quit, round-eye?

67
00:07:48.167 --> 00:07:49.917
Not yet.

68
00:07:51.083 --> 00:07:53.083
Go practice your katas.

69
00:07:54.625 --> 00:07:57.000
How come you coach him but not me?

70
00:07:57.167 --> 00:08:00.708
I brought you here to help me
train my son. Don't question me!

71
00:08:00.875 --> 00:08:04.542
If you expect me to be his punching bag,
you can forget about our deal.

72
00:08:05.625 --> 00:08:07.542
[BOYS SHOUTING]

73
00:08:11.333 --> 00:08:12.458
Yeah! Throw a punch.

74
00:08:12.625 --> 00:08:14.958
[CHILDREN SHOUTING]

75
00:08:28.083 --> 00:08:29.917
Some day,

76
00:08:30.083 --> 00:08:33.167
I'll fight in the <i>kumite</i>
and make my father proud.

77
00:08:44.292 --> 00:08:48.792
FRANK: Shidoshi, I feel like I've lost
part of my family, too.

78
00:08:48.958 --> 00:08:53.583
Shingo and I were
close friends, brothers.

79
00:08:53.750 --> 00:08:58.167
And you and Mrs. Tanaka
have treated me...

80
00:08:59.250 --> 00:09:00.875
...like a son.

81
00:09:05.375 --> 00:09:07.458
What will happen now?

82
00:09:08.583 --> 00:09:12.500
No more training.
I stop now.

83
00:09:17.083 --> 00:09:19.708
But you have so much to teach.

84
00:09:21.208 --> 00:09:22.917
TANAKA: You don't understand.

85
00:09:24.375 --> 00:09:28.250
In the war, I lost my first family:

86
00:09:28.417 --> 00:09:32.583
My son, daughter and wife.

87
00:09:35.375 --> 00:09:37.750
They live in Hiroshima.

88
00:09:40.667 --> 00:09:44.208
I left Japan because of the war.

89
00:09:44.375 --> 00:09:46.625
War was wrong.

90
00:09:46.792 --> 00:09:50.750
I came here to start over.

91
00:09:50.917 --> 00:09:54.667
Begin a new family, with a son,

92
00:09:54.833 --> 00:09:57.875
another chance to pass on the teaching.

93
00:09:59.000 --> 00:10:00.750
For 2,000 years,

94
00:10:00.917 --> 00:10:04.750
knowledge passed from father to son,

95
00:10:04.917 --> 00:10:07.042
father to son.

96
00:10:09.833 --> 00:10:14.500
When Shingo died, it stopped.

97
00:10:18.125 --> 00:10:21.333
Teach me.
I can do it.

98
00:10:21.500 --> 00:10:24.750
You are not Japanese!
You are not a Tanaka!

99
00:10:24.917 --> 00:10:28.458
You taught me,
using any technique that works,

100
00:10:28.625 --> 00:10:31.500
never to limit myself to one style,

101
00:10:31.667 --> 00:10:35.417
- to keep an open mind.
- Why?

102
00:10:37.250 --> 00:10:40.625
To honor you, <i>Shidoshi.</i>

103
00:10:41.750 --> 00:10:44.167
[FRANK GRUNTING]

104
00:11:17.375 --> 00:11:21.000
[BOTH GRUNTING]

105
00:11:38.417 --> 00:11:40.250
[FRANK GRUNTING]

106
00:11:49.208 --> 00:11:50.750
[GRUNTS]

107
00:11:53.292 --> 00:11:54.875
[FRANK GRUNTS]

108
00:12:00.750 --> 00:12:02.250
[INHALES DEEPLY]

109
00:12:02.417 --> 00:12:03.250
[EXHALES]

110
00:13:16.625 --> 00:13:18.250
[GRUNTS]

111
00:13:21.917 --> 00:13:23.625
[EXHALES]

112
00:13:30.792 --> 00:13:32.542
[GRUNTS]

113
00:13:35.083 --> 00:13:37.833
Practice until you can meditate.

114
00:13:38.000 --> 00:13:39.750
Nothing can distract you,

115
00:13:39.917 --> 00:13:44.292
so that you see and feel nothing
except your own energy.

116
00:13:46.292 --> 00:13:48.958
[FRANK EXHALES]

117
00:13:49.125 --> 00:13:51.458
[SCREAMING]

118
00:13:52.542 --> 00:13:54.667
[SCREAMING]

119
00:14:21.792 --> 00:14:24.583
[GRUNTING]

120
00:16:58.417 --> 00:17:00.958
Are you awake, Shidoshi?

121
00:17:02.292 --> 00:17:04.500
Do you sleep with your eyes open?

122
00:17:04.667 --> 00:17:06.583
How are you feeling?

123
00:17:08.042 --> 00:17:09.042
[SIGHS]

124
00:17:09.208 --> 00:17:12.500
Like a old man.

125
00:17:12.667 --> 00:17:14.750
And how about you?

126
00:17:17.083 --> 00:17:21.000
- I am going to Hong Kong.
- You're sure you want to do this?

127
00:17:22.000 --> 00:17:27.417
To honor you means everything to me.

128
00:17:28.292 --> 00:17:31.167
I have poured all my knowledge into you.

129
00:17:31.333 --> 00:17:36.333
When you fight,
my spirit fight with you.

130
00:17:36.500 --> 00:17:40.917
In kumite, you will need it.

131
00:18:19.167 --> 00:18:23.083
JACKSON: Hey, babe.
Want to go out with a real "big man"?

132
00:18:23.250 --> 00:18:24.833
No, huh?

133
00:18:31.042 --> 00:18:34.667
Too handsome for you, huh, honey?

134
00:18:39.000 --> 00:18:41.625
WOMAN: This your first time
in Hong Kong?

135
00:18:41.792 --> 00:18:44.292
You two are here for the kumite,
aren't you?

136
00:18:44.458 --> 00:18:47.958
<i>Kumite?</i> What is <i>kumite?</i>

137
00:18:48.125 --> 00:18:51.458
Look, guys, I know there's
a secret, full-contact event

138
00:18:51.625 --> 00:18:53.875
being held in Hong Kong
in the next few days.

139
00:18:54.042 --> 00:18:58.708
- Yes. Hong Kong is an exciting city.
- I also happen to know a little bit

140
00:18:58.875 --> 00:19:00.667
about some of your competition.

141
00:19:02.625 --> 00:19:07.458
OK. Would you just tell me
how you got invited?

142
00:19:09.000 --> 00:19:12.042
[MEN SPEAKING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

143
00:19:12.208 --> 00:19:13.875
Thanks, guys.

144
00:19:15.458 --> 00:19:17.125
[LAUGHS]

145
00:19:20.958 --> 00:19:22.417
[ARCADE GAME BEEPS]

146
00:19:22.583 --> 00:19:25.708
What, think you can
give me some competition?

147
00:19:25.875 --> 00:19:28.250
Sure, I'll try it.

148
00:19:28.417 --> 00:19:31.917
That's what I like to hear,
a kid who isn't afraid to lose.

149
00:19:32.083 --> 00:19:34.833
No, no, I got it.
I won't take your money.

150
00:19:36.667 --> 00:19:39.083
- You ready?
- Yeah.

151
00:19:42.875 --> 00:19:45.625
[GAME PLAYING INDISTINCTLY]

152
00:20:06.708 --> 00:20:09.458
- You like this kind of fighting, huh?
- Yeah.

153
00:20:09.625 --> 00:20:13.250
You want to see some real fighting,
you can see me fight at the <i>kumite.</i>

154
00:20:13.417 --> 00:20:16.250
I'm here, too, for the <i>kumite.</i>

155
00:20:16.417 --> 00:20:18.750
Aren't you a little young
for full contact?

156
00:20:18.917 --> 00:20:22.875
Aren't you a little old
for video games?

157
00:20:23.042 --> 00:20:25.708
- You want to go at it again, huh?
- Yeah.

158
00:20:25.875 --> 00:20:28.250
[JACKSON SIGHS]

159
00:20:39.583 --> 00:20:43.458
- Not bad, kid. Name's Ray Jackson.
- I'm Frank Dux.

160
00:20:52.167 --> 00:20:54.958
- Mrs. Tanaka.
- Mrs. Tanaka?

161
00:20:55.125 --> 00:20:56.167
Yes?

162
00:20:56.333 --> 00:20:58.375
HELMER: It's very important
to the government

163
00:20:58.542 --> 00:21:01.208
of the United States
that we find Frank Dux.

164
00:21:01.375 --> 00:21:04.875
We understand he might
have visited here recently.

165
00:21:05.083 --> 00:21:09.958
- Mr. Tanaka is very ill.
- We're sorry to hear that.

166
00:21:10.125 --> 00:21:15.042
- Was Frank here recently?
- Frank came here to pay his respects.

167
00:21:15.208 --> 00:21:17.208
- When was that?
- Two days ago.

168
00:21:17.375 --> 00:21:20.833
Did he say, or do you know
if he was going to Hong Kong?

169
00:21:21.000 --> 00:21:24.125
- I don't know.
- Of course you know.

170
00:21:24.292 --> 00:21:26.375
Look, we're not trying...

171
00:21:26.542 --> 00:21:29.375
We're very sorry to have disturbed you.

172
00:21:29.542 --> 00:21:31.667
Thank you very much for your time.

173
00:21:38.500 --> 00:21:40.125
MAN: May I help you?

174
00:21:40.292 --> 00:21:43.250
My name is Jackson. This is
Mr. Frank Dux. Our rooms ready?

175
00:21:43.417 --> 00:21:47.208
Mr. Lin in room 310
wants to see you after you check in.

176
00:21:47.375 --> 00:21:49.292
Who the hell is Mr. Lin?

177
00:21:49.458 --> 00:21:52.833
I'm Lin. You Jackson?
You look like a Jackson.

178
00:21:55.667 --> 00:22:00.125
- That would make you Frank Ducks.
- No, no, no. It's Dux.

179
00:22:00.292 --> 00:22:02.458
Gotcha!
Like "put up your dukes," right?

180
00:22:02.625 --> 00:22:06.750
OK, so here's the deal.
This is the biggest <i>kumite</i> ever.

181
00:22:06.917 --> 00:22:11.042
We got fighters from all over.
I've been assigned by the IFAA

182
00:22:11.208 --> 00:22:15.500
to help you and the other North American
fighters find your way around.

183
00:22:15.667 --> 00:22:18.125
I'm going to make sure
you guys give it your best

184
00:22:18.292 --> 00:22:21.250
and don't disqualify by fighting
outside the arena.

185
00:22:22.458 --> 00:22:25.292
LIN: The triad, they are like the mafia,

186
00:22:25.458 --> 00:22:28.417
is allowing us to hold
<i>kumite</i> here this time.

187
00:22:32.542 --> 00:22:37.125
Here it comes, men, the war city.
Not a place for outsiders.

188
00:22:37.292 --> 00:22:41.375
You are in Hong Kong, but you are
about to cross an invisible border

189
00:22:41.542 --> 00:22:43.167
into Mainland China.

190
00:22:43.333 --> 00:22:46.958
No joke, man.
It's a rundown piece of no-man's land

191
00:22:47.125 --> 00:22:51.042
in the middle of a tourist paradise.
Goes way back to the old lease agreement

192
00:22:51.208 --> 00:22:53.375
between Great Britain and China.

193
00:22:53.542 --> 00:22:56.583
Once you step out of the sunlight
into the narrow corridors,

194
00:22:56.750 --> 00:22:59.292
it's time to protect your nuts, guys.

195
00:23:04.250 --> 00:23:07.708
[LIN SPEAKING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

196
00:23:10.542 --> 00:23:12.500
OK, USA!

197
00:23:14.083 --> 00:23:16.125
OK, USA.

198
00:23:33.208 --> 00:23:35.250
[BABY CRYING IN DISTANCE]

199
00:23:35.417 --> 00:23:37.375
[WOMAN SHOUTING
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

200
00:23:37.542 --> 00:23:40.375
[MEN CHATTERING
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

201
00:23:45.125 --> 00:23:47.917
[RATS SQUEAKING]

202
00:23:56.792 --> 00:23:58.792
[MEN CHATTERING
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

203
00:25:24.583 --> 00:25:29.458
OK, guys, first, you can show the
Black Dragon Boys your invitation.

204
00:25:29.625 --> 00:25:33.042
Then you got to qualify
and prove to them

205
00:25:33.208 --> 00:25:35.750
you can step onto the runway
and not get killed.

206
00:25:35.917 --> 00:25:37.875
Got it?

207
00:25:38.042 --> 00:25:40.000
You got it?

208
00:25:40.167 --> 00:25:42.250
FRANK: Mm-hm.

209
00:25:59.042 --> 00:26:02.917
It says he represents the Tanaka clan.

210
00:26:03.083 --> 00:26:05.542
You don't look like Tanaka.

211
00:26:05.708 --> 00:26:09.250
- <i>Shidoshi</i> Tanaka trained me.
- What's the hold-up?

212
00:26:09.417 --> 00:26:12.875
He says Senzo Tanaka is his <i>shidoshi.</i>

213
00:26:13.042 --> 00:26:16.083
What's the difference
if Bruce Springsteen is his <i>shidoshi?</i>

214
00:26:16.250 --> 00:26:21.375
If Senzo Tanaka is his <i>shidoshi,</i>
then show us the <i>dim mak.</i>

215
00:26:21.542 --> 00:26:26.042
- What the hell is a <i>dim mack?</i>
- Death touch.

216
00:26:34.458 --> 00:26:35.958
Thanks.

217
00:26:37.000 --> 00:26:40.125
Vic, choose a brick.

218
00:26:40.292 --> 00:26:41.875
OK, Frank.

219
00:26:43.542 --> 00:26:45.375
What about this one?

220
00:26:52.542 --> 00:26:54.167
No!

221
00:26:56.583 --> 00:26:58.458
Bottom one.

222
00:27:27.583 --> 00:27:29.917
[GRUNTS]

223
00:27:30.708 --> 00:27:32.542
Whoa, yeah!

224
00:27:37.875 --> 00:27:41.958
Son of the bitch!
Is that good enough, guys?

225
00:27:43.042 --> 00:27:45.125
We honor your invitation.

226
00:27:45.292 --> 00:27:47.292
No shit, you honor his invitation!

227
00:27:49.667 --> 00:27:51.208
That was great!

228
00:27:58.250 --> 00:28:03.125
Very good... but brick not hit back.

229
00:28:21.375 --> 00:28:24.125
RAWLINS: Here's a picture of
the man that we're looking for.

230
00:28:24.292 --> 00:28:27.625
His name is Frank Dux.

231
00:28:27.792 --> 00:28:31.250
We have reason to believe
Frank is here in Hong Kong.

232
00:28:31.417 --> 00:28:35.250
His name was on a list on a flight
from San Francisco two days ago.

233
00:28:35.417 --> 00:28:39.875
Two days ago? Maybe he already left,
went somewhere else.

234
00:28:40.042 --> 00:28:41.750
Asia's a very big place, you know.

235
00:28:41.917 --> 00:28:44.750
We were hoping you'd hold
onto this for reference.

236
00:28:44.917 --> 00:28:47.500
We're here because Frank
is going to fight in the kumite,

237
00:28:47.667 --> 00:28:49.958
and we're here to stop him.

238
00:28:52.208 --> 00:28:55.875
<i>- The kumite?</i>
- Yes.

239
00:29:10.583 --> 00:29:13.292
Inspector Chen, we all know

240
00:29:13.458 --> 00:29:16.208
that the <i>kumite</i>
is happening here in Hong Kong,

241
00:29:16.375 --> 00:29:19.500
and we all know it's going on
over the next three days.

242
00:29:20.708 --> 00:29:23.833
Look, all we want you to do
is pass this picture out to your men.

243
00:29:24.000 --> 00:29:26.583
They spot Dux, they give us a call.

244
