00:57:32.875 --> 00:57:34.083
[GROANS]

490
00:57:59.917 --> 00:58:02.625
[BOTH GRUNTING]

491
00:58:18.125 --> 00:58:19.833
[FRANK GROANS]

492
00:58:29.292 --> 00:58:31.042
[YELLS]

493
00:58:35.917 --> 00:58:37.292
[MAN GROANS]

494
00:59:17.875 --> 00:59:21.417
[FRANK YELLING]

495
00:59:53.125 --> 00:59:57.958
[ALL CHEERING]

496
01:00:01.417 --> 01:00:03.917
All right, Frankie! Yeah!

497
01:00:06.667 --> 01:00:10.042
ALL: [CHANTING]
Dux! Dux! Dux! Dux!

498
01:00:18.625 --> 01:00:20.417
Time to separate the men from the boys.

499
01:00:20.583 --> 01:00:24.667
Just be careful Chong Li doesn't
separate your head from your body.

500
01:00:25.417 --> 01:00:29.167
- Go for the gut. He's soft there.
- What the hell are you talking about?

501
01:00:29.333 --> 01:00:33.333
Chong Li's weak in the gut.
That's how Parades surprised him.

502
01:00:33.500 --> 01:00:34.750
Hey, you listen to me.

503
01:00:34.917 --> 01:00:38.875
Go for the stomach
and stay away from his right leg.

504
01:00:39.042 --> 01:00:42.042
Will you stop worrying?
I've got it under control.

505
01:00:42.208 --> 01:00:45.625
You sound like my mother.
Man alive!

506
01:00:51.083 --> 01:00:52.458
[REFEREE SHOUTS
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

507
01:00:54.958 --> 01:00:56.958
[REFEREE SHOUTS
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

508
01:00:57.917 --> 01:00:59.708
[REFEREE SHOUTS
THEN JACKSON YELLS]

509
01:01:06.042 --> 01:01:08.208
[JACKSON GRUNTING]

510
01:01:08.375 --> 01:01:09.667
I Got him!

511
01:01:09.833 --> 01:01:12.417
What are you doing?
Keep going.

512
01:01:12.583 --> 01:01:15.917
Jackson! Jackson! Jackson!

513
01:01:21.292 --> 01:01:25.333
Cheer for him now! He's dead!
I got him! Yeah!

514
01:01:25.500 --> 01:01:29.708
Yeah! Yeah!

515
01:01:31.708 --> 01:01:34.250
Yeah.

516
01:01:34.417 --> 01:01:37.167
[JACKSON GRUNTING]

517
01:01:40.542 --> 01:01:41.875
[JACKSON GROANS]

518
01:01:44.583 --> 01:01:48.000
No! Stop!

519
01:02:04.500 --> 01:02:08.000
ALL: [CHANTING]
Chong Li! Chong Li! Chong Li!

520
01:02:14.167 --> 01:02:15.333
Come back, Frank!

521
01:02:54.542 --> 01:02:58.708
Ray? Ray, I'm here.

522
01:02:58.875 --> 01:03:01.000
Ray?

523
01:03:01.167 --> 01:03:04.333
The doctor says
you are going to be OK.

524
01:03:04.500 --> 01:03:07.667
You are lucky you have
a head like a rock.

525
01:03:07.833 --> 01:03:10.500
Yeah. You'll be out
of here in a week.

526
01:03:13.417 --> 01:03:17.542
I'll get back at Chong Li.
That's a promise.

527
01:03:17.708 --> 01:03:20.917
JANICE: You think that's what he wants?
Someone to share a room with?

528
01:03:21.083 --> 01:03:23.708
Janice, stay out of this.

529
01:03:23.875 --> 01:03:26.417
Frank, I don't want
to see you get hurt.

530
01:03:26.583 --> 01:03:27.917
Then don't watch.

531
01:03:28.083 --> 01:03:30.375
If you want to argue,
go elsewhere, please.

532
01:03:32.167 --> 01:03:33.250
Sorry.

533
01:03:36.500 --> 01:03:39.708
You're not even trying to understand
what this means to us.

534
01:03:39.875 --> 01:03:43.333
What is there to understand
about guys who have to prove themselves

535
01:03:43.500 --> 01:03:46.917
- by beating each other's brains?
- Why did you become a reporter?

536
01:03:47.083 --> 01:03:50.125
- What does that have to do with it?
- Answer the question!

537
01:03:50.292 --> 01:03:54.708
My father was a reporter. I was a good
writer. It seemed like the right thing.

538
01:03:54.875 --> 01:03:59.333
And you want to be the best reporter you
can be, for him and yourself, right?

539
01:03:59.500 --> 01:04:00.750
Yes, that's right.

540
01:04:00.917 --> 01:04:03.917
Well, I'm just trying
to be the best I can be.

541
01:04:04.083 --> 01:04:07.250
Not just for me,
for Tanaka, my <i>shidoshi,</i> too.

542
01:04:07.417 --> 01:04:10.958
Great, Frank. That's just great!
Go right ahead!

543
01:04:11.125 --> 01:04:14.000
I just hope you don't end up
like Jackson or worse.

544
01:04:14.167 --> 01:04:17.417
But I'm not going to
stand around and watch it!

545
01:04:20.583 --> 01:04:24.792
You're blowing it, Frank.
Forget about the girl.

546
01:04:24.958 --> 01:04:27.708
Forget about getting back
at Chong Li for Ray.

547
01:04:27.875 --> 01:04:30.708
You have a chance
to take it all tomorrow.

548
01:04:30.875 --> 01:04:34.000
You can be the first
Westerner to win this thing,

549
01:04:34.167 --> 01:04:36.833
but you got to have a clear head.
You hear me?

550
01:04:38.125 --> 01:04:40.458
You hear me?

551
01:04:47.083 --> 01:04:48.792
[CHEN SPEAKS IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

552
01:04:48.958 --> 01:04:51.333
Why are you interested
in stopping the kumite?

553
01:04:51.500 --> 01:04:54.625
Someone almost got killed there today.

554
01:04:54.792 --> 01:04:58.417
I have a friend fighting in it.
I don't want him to get hurt.

555
01:04:58.583 --> 01:05:00.250
[OFFICER SPEAKS
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

556
01:05:00.917 --> 01:05:05.833
[BOTH SPEAK IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

557
01:05:09.208 --> 01:05:15.000
- Who is your friend?
- His name is... Frank Dux.

558
01:05:32.875 --> 01:05:34.208
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

559
01:05:41.750 --> 01:05:42.583
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

560
01:07:26.917 --> 01:07:30.458
[CHATTERING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

561
01:07:36.292 --> 01:07:40.167
[LAUGHING]

562
01:07:49.542 --> 01:07:51.417
You guys here for the finals?

563
01:07:51.583 --> 01:07:54.208
There aren't going
to be any finals, Dux.

564
01:07:54.375 --> 01:07:57.958
- At least, not for you.
- Don't try to stop me.

565
01:07:58.125 --> 01:08:00.708
We're not. He will.

566
01:08:04.167 --> 01:08:06.958
I did not come this far to stop now.

567
01:08:07.125 --> 01:08:10.333
You shouldn't have come
in the first place. Take him.

568
01:08:10.833 --> 01:08:13.000
[SPEAKS IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

569
01:08:40.583 --> 01:08:43.125
You're really being
a hard-ass about this.

570
01:08:43.292 --> 01:08:44.875
- Careful.
- Put these on

571
01:08:45.042 --> 01:08:48.083
- and we won't have to use them.
- The last warning, Frank.

572
01:08:49.333 --> 01:08:51.833
[ELECTRICITY BUZZING
THEN OFFICERS GROAN]

573
01:08:53.917 --> 01:08:56.583
Inspector, don't.
We've got to take him back.

574
01:08:58.333 --> 01:09:02.292
Would you give us a break? We've
been chasing you all over Hong Kong.

575
01:09:02.458 --> 01:09:06.917
OK, Frank, you win. But it's wrong
what you're doing. It's a mistake.

576
01:09:09.333 --> 01:09:12.167
I'll meet you at the airport...
tomorrow.

577
01:09:17.375 --> 01:09:20.625
Now what?
How are we going to stop him?

578
01:09:22.667 --> 01:09:24.083
Follow me.

579
01:09:28.917 --> 01:09:31.750
Time's up.
We can't wait any longer.

580
01:09:31.917 --> 01:09:35.000
Give me one more minute.
I give you my word. He'll be here.

581
01:09:35.167 --> 01:09:39.083
- We must follow the rules.
- Where is Mr. Dux?

582
01:09:39.250 --> 01:09:42.667
I wish everyone would just calm down.
I said he'll be here.

583
01:09:42.833 --> 01:09:45.625
- Too late.
- Too late?

584
01:09:45.792 --> 01:09:49.458
No such things as too late.

585
01:09:49.625 --> 01:09:51.958
LIN: Ah. Finally.

586
01:09:54.750 --> 01:09:57.083
- It's about fucking time!
- Sorry.

587
01:09:57.250 --> 01:10:01.500
- How do you feel today, Dux?
- Feel good. I am ready.

588
01:10:01.667 --> 01:10:03.292
Dux's my man.

589
01:10:03.458 --> 01:10:07.708
[CROWD CHATTERING]

590
01:10:47.500 --> 01:10:48.833
[REFEREE SHOUTS
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

591
01:10:50.708 --> 01:10:52.000
[REFEREE SHOUTS
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

592
01:10:54.625 --> 01:10:56.000
[REFEREE SHOUTS
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

